GraphQL
@ObjectType() --> tells GraphQL that this is a returnable model
@Field() --> Defaults to String
@InputType() --> marks this class as an input for Mutations
@Query() --> Queries fetch data
@Mutation() --> Mutations change data

In REST, you use Controllers to handle HTTP methods (GET, POST). In GraphQL, you use Resolvers to handle Queries (reading data) and Mutations (modifying data).


